{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Gracilidris'' | image = Gracilidris pombero casent0010797 profile 1.jpg | image_caption = ''G. pombero'' worker from [[Paraguay]] | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | classis = [[Insect]]a | ordo = [[Hymenoptera]] | familia = [[Ant|Formicidae]] | subfamilia = [[Dolichoderinae]] | tribus = [[Leptomyrmecini]] | genus = '''''Gracilidris''''' | genus_authority = [[Alexander L. Wild|Wild]] & [[Fabiana Cuezzo|Cuezzo]], 2006<ref>[http://osuc.biosci.ohio-state.edu/hymDB/nomenclator.name_entry?text_entry=Gracilidris ''Gracilidris''] in ''Hymenoptera Name Server''</ref> | subdivision_ranks = | subdivision = | type_species = ''Gracilidris pombero''<ref name="AWGracilidris"/> | diversity_link = #Species | diversity = 2 species | diversity_ref = <ref name="AntCat">{{AntCat|429105|Gracilidris|2014|accessdate=4 July 2014}}</ref> }}
'''''Gracilidris''''' is a [[genus]] of [[Dolichoderinae|dolichoderine]] [[ant]]s with nocturnal behaviour; thought to have gone extinct 15-20 million years ago, they have been found in [[Paraguay]], [[Brazil]], and [[Argentina]] and were described in 2006.<ref name=Wild>Wild, A. L. and F. Cuezzo. 2006. Rediscovery of a fossil Dolichoderine ant lineage (Hymenoptera: Formicidae: Dolichoderinae) and a description of a new genus from South America. ''Zootaxa'' '''1142''': 57-68. ISSN: [http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/ 1175-5334] '''[http://www.antwiki.org/wiki/images/c/c2/Wild_%26_Cuezzo_2006.pdf PDF]'''</ref>
The single existing fossil in [[Dominican amber]] makes the genus a [[Lazarus taxon]]. The only known extant species, ''[[Gracilidris pombero]]'', nests in small [[ant colony|colonies]] in the soil. These ants have been described only very recently and little is known about them.{{citation needed|date=July 2014}}
==Species== * †''[[Gracilidris humiloides]]'' <small>(Wilson, 1985)</small> * ''[[Gracilidris pombero]]'' <small>Wild & Cuezzo, 2006</small>
